160 - WDPRO Ticket Terms & Conditions DL.text: Each Disney eTicket allows one entry at a DisneylandÂ® Theme Park turnstile. Upon entry, the Guest will be provided with a standard Theme Park ticket for use for the applicable purchased days. Disney is not responsible for any loss or inconvenience caused by computer or mobile device error, or unauthorized duplication or sale of any Disney eTicket. In the event that duplicate Disney eTickets are presented for theme park admission, Disney reserves the right to refuse entry.

120 - WDPRO Ticket Terms & Conditions DL.text: Tickets may not be sold, bartered nor exchanged for goods, services or benefits, and must be used by the same person on any and all days. Hand stamp and standard ticket are required for same day readmission to same Park and, if applicable, crossover to the other Park. Disney is not responsible for lost or stolen tickets or property. Theme parks, restaurants, attractions, entertainment or other recreation or services may change operating hours; close due to refurbishing, capacity, weather or special events; and may otherwise change or be discontinued without notice and without liability. Tickets are not valid for special or premier events or other activities which are separately priced or for special events that are not open to the general public. Disney shall not be liable for non-utilization of ticket components or loss of recreational opportunities due to refurbishing, capacity, inclement weather, special events or any circumstances beyond their control. Guests must obey all safety signage, instructions and rules. Entry into a Theme Park constitutes consent for Disney to use any film, video or likeness of bearer for any purpose whatsoever without payment to the bearer. It is agreed between the owners of the DisneylandÂ® Resort and ticket users that all claims for injury or loss arising incident to the presence of the ticket users on owners' property shall be litigated in Orange County, California. Disney reserves the right to refuse admittance to any person or persons.

150 - WDPRO Ticket Terms & Conditions DL.text: All features of tickets are subject to change without notice. Other restrictions may apply.

140 - WDPRO Ticket Terms & Conditions DL.text: Multi-day tickets purchased online expire 13 days after first use and each day of use of a ticket constitutes one full day of use. Unused tickets purchased online expire on the dates set forth on such tickets. Childrenâ€™s tickets may only be used by persons three (3) to nine (9) years of age.

110 - WDPRO Ticket Terms & Conditions DL.text: Due to various restrictions and limitations, tickets cannot be shipped to all locations. Title to the tickets passes upon delivery of the tickets to the shipper. Additional charges apply based on delivery method chosen, and on international orders

100 - WDPRO Ticket Terms & Conditions DL.text: Tickets are nonrefundable and revocable. All prices are in US dollars. Ticket orders are not accepted until confirmed with confirmation number. All rates are net rates and subject to change without notice as required by law for any applicable California State taxes.

130 - WDPRO Ticket Terms & Conditions DL.text: Disney reserves the right to cancel the sale of any tickets prior to the confirmation of the purchase of such tickets or prior to the shipment of the tickets. Tickets are nonrefundable and revocable.

200 - Magic Morning DLR.text:
Magic Morning allows one early admission to select attractions, stores, entertainment and dining locations at Disneyland Park on select days one hour before the park opens to the general public.

For admission, a Guest (age 3 or older) must have a qualifying 3-day or longer Disneyland Resort theme park ticket purchased in advance of arrival. To enhance the Magic Morning experience, please arrive at least one hour and 15 minutes prior to regular park opening.

Magic Morning early admission is based on availability and does not operate daily. Check Disneyland.com for schedule. Applicable theme park days and times of operation and all other elements including, but not limited to, operation of attractions, entertainment, stores and restaurants and appearances of Characters may vary and are subject to change without notice. Subject to capacity, cancellation and other restrictions.

TKT-PR-100-1-Park-Per-Day-Mobile-DLR.text:
This ticket is valid for admission to 1 parkâ€”either Disneyland Park or Disney California Adventure Parkâ€”but not both in the same day.

One-day tickets are valid now through December 31, 2016.

Hand stamp and standard ticket are required for same day readmission to same park. Admit one. Other restrictions apply.

TKT-PR-100-Multi-Day-Park-Mobile-DLR.text:
This ticket is valid for admission to 1 park each dayâ€”either Disneyland Park or Disney California Adventure Parkâ€”but not both in the same day.

The first day of use of this ticket must be on or before December 31, 2016. This ticket must be used within 13 days of first use or by January 13, 2017, whichever occurs first.

Hand stamp and standard ticket are required for same day readmission to same park. Admit one. Other restrictions apply.

The first day of use of this ticket must be on or before December 31, 2016. This ticket must be used within 13 days of first use or by January 13, 2017, whichever occurs first.

Hand stamp and standard ticket are required for same day readmission to same park and entry to the other park. Admit one. Other restrictions apply.
